race.comment: Looks a wide open contest. ALTERMATUM (24) is a very consistent conveyance who is yet to miss the top-five in 14 career starts and doesn't know how to put in a poor one. Drawn to get a soft run from gate two and gets in on the minimum weight. Should be right there when the judge calls a halt. The well-related SILVER WEDDING (4) (full to G1 winner Schwarz) has put back-to-back wins together including one over this track and trip last time out. Hard to knock mares in form and has to come into calculations again. FLYING AURELIUS (9) is one from one when second-up from the break and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Among the leading hopes. CUTEPI (10) went down by the narrowest of margins at the latest outing and seems to be working up to another victory. In the mix. KADALL (3) has placed two from three around this circuit and may earn some minor money.
